# Instructions for modifications to the entire project

## First rule
- DO NOT MODIFY THE .cursorrules file YOU CAN DO IT ONLY WHEN CLEARLY SPECIFIED.

## General Instructions
- All modifications should be made only in the requested section. Do not modify other sections.
- The project consists of 3 modules: ai_backend, db_backend, and client.
- The ai_backend module is responsible for interacting with the OpenAI API.
- The db_backend module is responsible for interacting with the database.
- The client module is responsible for interacting with the user.

## Folder and File Structure

### AI Backend (Python/FastAPI)
- main.py (Main FastAPI application)
- config.py (Configuration settings)
- app.py (Application logic)
- lesson_plan_generator.py (Lesson plan generation logic)
- intervention_note_improver.py (Note improvement logic)
- requirements.txt (Python dependencies)
- .env (Environment variables)
- vercel.json (Vercel deployment config)

### DB Backend (Node.js/Express)
- server.js (Main Express application)
- /api (API routes)
- /models (MongoDB models)
- /validators (Request validation)
- /middleware (Express middleware)
- /config (Configuration files)
- package.json (Node.js dependencies)
- .env (Environment variables)
- vercel.json (Vercel deployment config)

### Client (React/Vite)
- /src (React source code)
- /public (Static assets)
- /build (Production build)
- package.json (Node.js dependencies)
- tsconfig.json (TypeScript config)
- webpack.config.js (Webpack config)
- .env.development (Development env vars)
- .env.production (Production env vars)

## Instructions for modifications to the  API Backends modifications
ai_backend
        -default model: gpt-4o-mini
        -model for more complex tasks: gpt-4o
        -forbidden models: gpt-4
        -responsibility: "OpenAI API interactions only",
        -allowed_operations: ["OpenAI API calls", "Request handling", "Response streaming"],
        -forbidden_operations: ["Database operations", "File storage", "Authentication"]

    "db_backend/*"
        -"responsibility": "Database operations only",
        -"allowed_operations": "MongoDB operations", "Data validation", "Authentication",
        -"forbidden_operations": "OpenAI API calls", "AI model interactions"


